&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Self Publishing</span><hr size=1> Well first off ditch the publishing house idea. Right off the bat thats just a bad idea unless you're positive you'll sell tons of copies. I haven't seen any of your work, if I have it was probably when I was lurking about two years ago so. . .I hope you can deliver an acceptable quality. No offense its just that my advise won't help otherwise.<br><br>Anyway this is one of my favorite things to talk about so I've got a few ideas. <br><br>You can print out those 60 copies (100 preferably) on your own by going to a print shop. There are some that will even do a comic/manga type binding for you. This initial cost will be pretty much all you'll ever spend. At least the bulk of it. The good thing about going this way is that you won't owe any money to a publishing house or have them take a percentage. The downside is that you lose the distribution power a publishing house would have. But for now, since you said you just want to try it out, this is negligible and probably totally irrelevant.<br><br>I say irrelevant because you won't have the need for a large distribution, and they WILL make you pay for as much as they can off of the profit. Then they split the rest of it with you. Now I take it you have an interest in manga? Ok Ok dumb question. What you can do is go to a manga/anime specialty shop. In smaller areas these guys are the only places that people interested in that kind of stuff can go. Where I live we have a Goku store. Mostly DBZ but, you can find everything else there as well. Now go to this store and offer them a consignment. They carry your comic and take a percentage of the profit when its sold. You take what isn't sold back. Only downside of this is that your wares may be mangled from all the browsers flipping through the pages. Upside includes: you will have a set percentage and it will be considerably higher than other methods i.e. they buy from you for 50 cents and sell on their own for their price like 1.50. You will still get exposure even if no one buys if you include a place they can reach you. E-mail for instance.<br><br>Now the grand scheme of it all is that you can sell a bit of advertising space in your comic that may even pay for the printing costs. A videogame store, a manga/anime store or any other thing that may interest your desired demographic. Heck you could even offer to design the ad or something even if they wouldn't like to advertise in your comic.<br><br>This method is cheaper and much more fufilling but it does require some people skills not to mention the drawing ability that goes without saying.<br><br>I hope I've helped you in some way and I'll answer any questions you might have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubrolly711.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brolly711</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/29/02 10:10:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3667.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Self Publishing</span><hr size=1> If you ask me selling the comics does not involve much talent and the best pictures, its the story that count. For example: Dragon Ball started as a comic and the drawing were not the best... it even looked rushed sometimes. However the story was amazing and people liked the idea of a power young boy looking for dragon balls and they liked the adventures he had.<br><br>So basicly... make sure you have a good story line. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neon>neon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/29/02 10:28:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3667.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://liquid2k.com/nld/Gaara.jpg height=119 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Self Publishing</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You can print out those 60 copies (100 preferably) on your own by going to a print shop.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Well that's what I originally had in mind, and that's what I'm going to go with, I just needed some lists of prices and stuff on cost of printing.<br>Its completely self financed and driven, I'm going to pay for everything myself and hopefully break even.<br><br>As for my art quality, no bragging intended but people didn't call me the reigning champion of fight club for nothing ^_^.<br><br>Thanks for you help.<br> <p>::HAPPY GO LUCKY!!!::</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uascendedbob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascended Bob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/30/02 2:30:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3667.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Self Publishing</span><hr size=1> Well I hope you do well. I think a nice average mark-up would be 300%. So I don't know how much printing costs are globally but, you can do the math. It'll pay for itself if you sell close to half. <br><br>Hope to see some artwork. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufluxhavoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FluxHavoc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=1